# 🚀 Image Captioning using Deep Learning

## 📌 Overview

This project implements an **end-to-end Image Captioning system** that generates natural language descriptions for images by combining **Computer Vision and Natural Language Processing** techniques.

The model uses a **CNN encoder (Xception)** to extract visual features and an **LSTM-based decoder** to generate captions word-by-word.

---

## 🧠 Model Architecture

The model follows an **Encoder–Decoder architecture** combining Computer Vision and NLP.

---

### 🔹 Image Encoder (CNN)

- Pretrained **Xception model** (without top layer)
- Extracts a **2048-dimensional feature vector**
- Feature processing:
  - Dropout layer
  - Dense layer (2048 → 256)

---

### 🔹 Text Decoder (LSTM)

- Input: tokenized caption sequences (max length = 34)
- Embedding layer:
  - Converts words into **256-dimensional vectors**
- Dropout layer for regularization
- LSTM layer:
  - Learns sequential dependencies
  - Outputs a **256-dimensional context vector**

---

### 🔹 Feature Fusion

- Combines image features and text features using:
  - **Element-wise addition (`Add` layer)**
- Followed by:
  - Dense layer (256 units, ReLU)

---

### 🔹 Output Layer

- Final Dense layer with **Softmax activation**
- Output size = vocabulary size (~7577 words)
- Predicts the **next word in the sequence**

---

### 📊 Model Summary

- Dual-input model:
  - Image features → shape `(None, 2048)`
  - Text sequence → shape `(None, 34)`
- Output:
  - Probability distribution over vocabulary

---


## 📂 Dataset

* **Flickr8k Dataset**
Dataset_images : [Download Images](https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1l0qNqT6H_0uhlWf3Sd9wekuh-s96srea?usp=sharing)
Dataset_texts : [Download](https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1roimV1VWSof25wGKCz0mudVdV_QbIR3i?usp=sharing)
  * ~8,000 images
  * Each image has 5 captions

---

## ⚙️ Features Implemented
  Tokens and features : [Download](https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1-qZS4IJD5dNexzSYnCsvxb-pxO8Pv6QR?usp=sharing)

* Image feature extraction using pretrained CNN (Xception)
* Text preprocessing:

  * Lowercasing, punctuation removal
  * Tokenization and vocabulary creation
  * Sequence padding
* Special tokens: `<start>` and `<end>`
* Custom **data generator using tf.data** for efficient training
* Model training with:

  * Categorical Cross-Entropy Loss
  * Adam Optimizer
  * Learning Rate Scheduling
  * Early Stopping

---

## 🏋️ Training Details

* **Loss Function:** Categorical Crossentropy
* **Optimizer:** Adam
* **Batch Size:** 32
* **Epochs:** 300
* **Feature Vector Size:** 2048 → 256

---

